{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GDDa9jnq6jNbonKE2hfEay","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01X6YtLQsfuWjPmZAkuMb9Ar","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/judy/output/push_notification_spec.md","content":"# Push Notification Spec — Trade Signal Alerts\n\n**Author:** Judy (Mobile Engineer)\n**Date:** 2026-04-03\n**Task:** T268\n**Status:** Final\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overview\n\nThis spec defines the push notification system for Kalshi trade signal alerts. Notifications fire when the trading pipeline generates high-confidence signals (≥80% confidence, per team consensus). Users are alerted on mobile (iOS/Android) and optionally via Slack webhook.\n\nSignal source: `GET http://localhost:3200/api/signals`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Trigger Conditions\n\nA notification is triggered when **all** of the following are true:\n\n| Condition | Rule |\n|-----------|------|\n| Signal confidence | `confidence >= 0.80` (team consensus minimum) |\n| Signal type | `signalType == \"entry\"` (not exit or hold) |\n| Market not already notified | No notification sent for same `marketId` + `side` in the last **15 minutes** |\n| Frequency limit not exceeded | Global cap: max **5 notifications per hour** across all markets |\n| Trading not in cooldown | Respect per-market cooldown window (see §5) |\n\n**Example triggering signal** (from live API):\n```json\n{\n  \"strategy\": \"mean_reversion\",\n  \"marketId\": \"m4\",\n  \"ticker\": \"BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\",\n  \"side\": \"yes\",\n  \"signalType\": \"entry\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"expectedEdge\": 23,\n  \"recommendedContracts\": 29,\n  \"riskAmount\": 1856,\n  \"reason\": \"Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890000\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Notification Payload Schema\n\n### 3.1 Mobile Push (APNs / FCM)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"notification\": {\n    \"title\": \"Trade Signal — BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\",\n    \"body\": \"BUY YES · 95% confidence · Edge: +23¢ · 29 contracts recommended\"\n  },\n  \"data\": {\n    \"type\": \"trade_signal\",\n    \"version\": \"1\",\n    \"marketId\": \"m4\",\n    \"ticker\": \"BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\",\n    \"marketTitle\": \"Will Bitcoin exceed $100,000 by June 30, 2026?\",\n    \"strategy\": \"mean_reversion\",\n    \"side\": \"yes\",\n    \"signalType\": \"entry\",\n    \"confidence\": 0.95,\n    \"expectedEdge\": 23,\n    \"currentPrice\": 64,\n    \"targetPrice\": 64,\n    \"recommendedContracts\": 29,\n    \"riskAmount\": 1856,\n    \"reason\": \"Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890000\",\n    \"generatedAt\": \"2026-04-03T18:29:52.840Z\",\n    \"deepLink\": \"agentplanet://signals/m4\"\n  },\n  \"apns\": {\n    \"headers\": {\n      \"apns-priority\": \"10\",\n      \"apns-push-type\": \"alert\",\n      \"apns-expiration\": \"300\"\n    },\n    \"payload\": {\n      \"aps\": {\n        \"alert\": {\n          \"title\": \"Trade Signal — BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\",\n          \"body\": \"BUY YES · 95% confidence · Edge: +23¢ · 29 contracts recommended\"\n        },\n        \"sound\": \"default\",\n        \"badge\": 1,\n        \"thread-id\": \"trade_signals\",\n        \"category\": \"TRADE_SIGNAL\",\n        \"mutable-content\": 1\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"android\": {\n    \"priority\": \"HIGH\",\n    \"ttl\": \"300s\",\n    \"notification\": {\n      \"channel_id\": \"trade_signals_high\",\n      \"icon\": \"ic_signal_alert\",\n      \"color\": \"#00C853\",\n      \"click_action\": \"OPEN_SIGNAL_DETAIL\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 3.2 Slack Webhook Payload\n\n```json\n{\n  \"text\": \"🟢 *Trade Signal Alert*\",\n  \"blocks\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"header\",\n      \"text\": {\n        \"type\": \"plain_text\",\n        \"text\": \"📈 Trade Signal — BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"section\",\n      \"fields\": [\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Strategy:*\\nmean_reversion\" },\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Side:*\\nBUY YES\" },\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Confidence:*\\n95%\" },\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Expected Edge:*\\n+23¢ per contract\" },\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Recommended:*\\n29 contracts\" },\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Risk Amount:*\\n$18.56\" }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"section\",\n      \"text\": {\n        \"type\": \"mrkdwn\",\n        \"text\": \"*Market:* Will Bitcoin exceed $100,000 by June 30, 2026?\\n*Reason:* Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890,000\\n*Current Price:* 64¢ YES\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"context\",\n      \"elements\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"mrkdwn\",\n          \"text\": \"Generated at 2026-04-03T18:29:52Z · Paper trading mode\"\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Delivery Channels\n\n### 4.1 Mobile Push\n\n| Platform | Service | Notes |\n|----------|---------|-------|\n| iOS | APNs (Apple Push Notification service) | `apns-priority: 10` for immediate delivery. TTL: 5 min (signals expire fast). Use `thread-id: \"trade_signals\"` to group notifications in Notification Center. |\n| Android | FCM (Firebase Cloud Messaging) | `priority: HIGH`, `channel_id: \"trade_signals_high\"` — users can mute per-channel without disabling all alerts. |\n\n**iOS Notification Actions** (`category: \"TRADE_SIGNAL\"`):\n- **View Signal** — opens signal detail screen (deep link: `agentplanet://signals/{marketId}`)\n- **Dismiss** — no action\n\n**Android Notification Channel**: `trade_signals_high`\n- Importance: `IMPORTANCE_HIGH` (heads-up display)\n- Sound: enabled by default\n- Vibration: enabled\n\n### 4.2 Slack Webhook\n\n- Webhook URL stored in environment variable `SLACK_SIGNAL_WEBHOOK_URL`\n- POST to webhook URL when signal fires\n- Include paper trading disclaimer until live trading is approved\n- Failures are logged but do not block mobile delivery\n\n### 4.3 Delivery Priority\n\n1. Mobile push (immediate, highest priority)\n2. Slack webhook (fire-and-forget, async)\n\n---\n\n## 5. Frequency Limits (Anti-Spam)\n\nThese limits prevent alert fatigue:\n\n| Scope | Limit | Window |\n|-------|-------|--------|\n| Same market + same side | 1 notification | 15 minutes |\n| Global (all markets combined) | 5 notifications | 60 minutes |\n| Per-user quiet hours | 0 notifications | 22:00–07:00 local time (configurable) |\n| Burst guard | 3 notifications | 5 minutes |\n\n**Cooldown logic:**\n```\nnotificationKey = \"{marketId}:{side}:{signalType}\"\nif lastNotified[notificationKey] exists AND (now - lastNotified[notificationKey]) < 15min:\n    skip — cooldown active\nelse:\n    fire notification\n    lastNotified[notificationKey] = now\n```\n\n**Hourly cap:**\n```\nhourlyCount = count of notifications fired in last 60 minutes\nif hourlyCount >= 5:\n    queue notification for next available slot (do not drop)\n    log: \"Hourly cap reached — notification queued\"\n```\n\n**Minimum confidence floor:** 0.80 (team consensus, see `public/consensus.md` entry #4). Never lower without backtesting.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Signal Evaluation Flow\n\n```\n[Signal Generator - port 3200]\n        │\n        ▼\n[GET /api/signals every 30s]\n        │\n        ▼\n[Filter: confidence >= 0.80?] ──No──▶ Drop\n        │ Yes\n        ▼\n[Filter: signalType == \"entry\"?] ──No──▶ Drop\n        │ Yes\n        ▼\n[Check cooldown: same marketId+side notified < 15 min ago?] ──Yes──▶ Skip\n        │ No\n        ▼\n[Check hourly cap: >= 5 in last 60 min?] ──Yes──▶ Queue\n        │ No\n        ▼\n[Build notification payload (§3)]\n        │\n        ├──▶ [Send APNs / FCM]\n        │\n        └──▶ [POST Slack webhook] (async, non-blocking)\n        │\n        ▼\n[Update lastNotified[key] = now]\n[Increment hourly counter]\n[Log delivery result]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Implementation Notes\n\n### Notification Service (suggested module: `agents/bob/backend/notification_service.js`)\n\n```javascript\n// Key environment variables\nAPNS_KEY_ID=...          // Apple key ID\nAPNS_TEAM_ID=...         // Apple team ID\nAPNS_KEY_PATH=...        // Path to .p8 key file\nAPNS_BUNDLE_ID=...       // com.agentplanet.app\nFCM_SERVER_KEY=...       // Firebase server key\nSLACK_SIGNAL_WEBHOOK_URL=...\n\n// Polling interval\nconst SIGNAL_POLL_INTERVAL_MS = 30_000; // 30 seconds\n\n// Thresholds\nconst MIN_CONFIDENCE = 0.80;\nconst COOLDOWN_MS = 15 * 60 * 1000;     // 15 minutes\nconst HOURLY_CAP = 5;\nconst BURST_CAP = 3;\nconst BURST_WINDOW_MS = 5 * 60 * 1000;\n```\n\n### Deep Linking\n\nApp must handle `agentplanet://signals/{marketId}` to open the signal detail screen.\n\n### Offline Handling\n\nIf the app is offline when a push arrives:\n- iOS: APNs stores the most recent notification per `apns-collapse-id: \"signal-{marketId}\"` — stale signals are replaced, not stacked.\n- Android: FCM stores latest per `collapse_key: \"signal-{marketId}\"`.\n\nSet `apns-expiration: 300` (5 minutes) — signals older than 5 minutes are irrelevant by the time the user sees them.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Paper Trading Disclaimer\n\nPer team consensus (`public/consensus.md` entry #1): all trading is in paper mode until live credentials are obtained. Push notifications must include context:\n\n- Mobile: Add subtitle \"Paper Trade · Not a live order\" when `executed: false`\n- Slack: Append \"Paper trading mode\" in context block\n\n---\n\n## 9. Open Questions for Bob/Mia\n\n1. **Auth token for device registration**: How will mobile devices register their push tokens with the backend? Suggest `POST /api/notifications/register` with `{ deviceToken, platform, userId }`.\n2. **User preferences**: Should users be able to filter by strategy, market category, or minimum edge? If yes, Bob needs a preferences store.\n3. **Webhook URL management**: One global Slack webhook or per-user? Suggest starting with global.\n\n---\n\n## 10. Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Notifications fire only for signals with `confidence >= 0.80`\n- [ ] Same market+side is not notified more than once per 15 minutes\n- [ ] Global cap of 5 notifications/hour is enforced\n- [ ] APNs payload validates against Apple's notification spec\n- [ ] FCM payload uses `HIGH` priority with correct channel\n- [ ] Slack webhook payload renders correctly in Slack\n- [ ] Notifications include paper trading disclaimer while `executed: false`\n- [ ] Stale signals (>5 min) are collapsed, not stacked on device\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":132,"cache_read_input_tokens":27221,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":132},"output_tokens":53,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0f295406-6ad6-41a7-a3ec-81f66d79253a","uuid":"85538b39-b379-43c0-ac7f-4ec89301d274"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X6YtLQsfuWjPmZAkuMb9Ar","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/judy/output/push_notification_spec.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0f295406-6ad6-41a7-a3ec-81f66d79253a","uuid":"8951fab9-35f3-4e6a-9bb0-07cffda4cda8","timestamp":"2026-04-03T18:32:55.051Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/judy/output/push_notification_spec.md","content":"# Push Notification Spec — Trade Signal Alerts\n\n**Author:** Judy (Mobile Engineer)\n**Date:** 2026-04-03\n**Task:** T268\n**Status:** Final\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overview\n\nThis spec defines the push notification system for Kalshi trade signal alerts. Notifications fire when the trading pipeline generates high-confidence signals (≥80% confidence, per team consensus). Users are alerted on mobile (iOS/Android) and optionally via Slack webhook.\n\nSignal source: `GET http://localhost:3200/api/signals`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Trigger Conditions\n\nA notification is triggered when **all** of the following are true:\n\n| Condition | Rule |\n|-----------|------|\n| Signal confidence | `confidence >= 0.80` (team consensus minimum) |\n| Signal type | `signalType == \"entry\"` (not exit or hold) |\n| Market not already notified | No notification sent for same `marketId` + `side` in the last **15 minutes** |\n| Frequency limit not exceeded | Global cap: max **5 notifications per hour** across all markets |\n| Trading not in cooldown | Respect per-market cooldown window (see §5) |\n\n**Example triggering signal** (from live API):\n```json\n{\n  \"strategy\": \"mean_reversion\",\n  \"marketId\": \"m4\",\n  \"ticker\": \"BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\",\n  \"side\": \"yes\",\n  \"signalType\": \"entry\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"expectedEdge\": 23,\n  \"recommendedContracts\": 29,\n  \"riskAmount\": 1856,\n  \"reason\": \"Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890000\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Notification Payload Schema\n\n### 3.1 Mobile Push (APNs / FCM)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"notification\": {\n    \"title\": \"Trade Signal — BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\",\n    \"body\": \"BUY YES · 95% confidence · Edge: +23¢ · 29 contracts recommended\"\n  },\n  \"data\": {\n    \"type\": \"trade_signal\",\n    \"version\": \"1\",\n    \"marketId\": \"m4\",\n    \"ticker\": \"BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\",\n    \"marketTitle\": \"Will Bitcoin exceed $100,000 by June 30, 2026?\",\n    \"strategy\": \"mean_reversion\",\n    \"side\": \"yes\",\n    \"signalType\": \"entry\",\n    \"confidence\": 0.95,\n    \"expectedEdge\": 23,\n    \"currentPrice\": 64,\n    \"targetPrice\": 64,\n    \"recommendedContracts\": 29,\n    \"riskAmount\": 1856,\n    \"reason\": \"Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890000\",\n    \"generatedAt\": \"2026-04-03T18:29:52.840Z\",\n    \"deepLink\": \"agentplanet://signals/m4\"\n  },\n  \"apns\": {\n    \"headers\": {\n      \"apns-priority\": \"10\",\n      \"apns-push-type\": \"alert\",\n      \"apns-expiration\": \"300\"\n    },\n    \"payload\": {\n      \"aps\": {\n        \"alert\": {\n          \"title\": \"Trade Signal — BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\",\n          \"body\": \"BUY YES · 95% confidence · Edge: +23¢ · 29 contracts recommended\"\n        },\n        \"sound\": \"default\",\n        \"badge\": 1,\n        \"thread-id\": \"trade_signals\",\n        \"category\": \"TRADE_SIGNAL\",\n        \"mutable-content\": 1\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"android\": {\n    \"priority\": \"HIGH\",\n    \"ttl\": \"300s\",\n    \"notification\": {\n      \"channel_id\": \"trade_signals_high\",\n      \"icon\": \"ic_signal_alert\",\n      \"color\": \"#00C853\",\n      \"click_action\": \"OPEN_SIGNAL_DETAIL\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 3.2 Slack Webhook Payload\n\n```json\n{\n  \"text\": \"🟢 *Trade Signal Alert*\",\n  \"blocks\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"header\",\n      \"text\": {\n        \"type\": \"plain_text\",\n        \"text\": \"📈 Trade Signal — BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"section\",\n      \"fields\": [\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Strategy:*\\nmean_reversion\" },\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Side:*\\nBUY YES\" },\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Confidence:*\\n95%\" },\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Expected Edge:*\\n+23¢ per contract\" },\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Recommended:*\\n29 contracts\" },\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Risk Amount:*\\n$18.56\" }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"section\",\n      \"text\": {\n        \"type\": \"mrkdwn\",\n        \"text\": \"*Market:* Will Bitcoin exceed $100,000 by June 30, 2026?\\n*Reason:* Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890,000\\n*Current Price:* 64¢ YES\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"context\",\n      \"elements\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"mrkdwn\",\n          \"text\": \"Generated at 2026-04-03T18:29:52Z · Paper trading mode\"\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Delivery Channels\n\n### 4.1 Mobile Push\n\n| Platform | Service | Notes |\n|----------|---------|-------|\n| iOS | APNs (Apple Push Notification service) | `apns-priority: 10` for immediate delivery. TTL: 5 min (signals expire fast). Use `thread-id: \"trade_signals\"` to group notifications in Notification Center. |\n| Android | FCM (Firebase Cloud Messaging) | `priority: HIGH`, `channel_id: \"trade_signals_high\"` — users can mute per-channel without disabling all alerts. |\n\n**iOS Notification Actions** (`category: \"TRADE_SIGNAL\"`):\n- **View Signal** — opens signal detail screen (deep link: `agentplanet://signals/{marketId}`)\n- **Dismiss** — no action\n\n**Android Notification Channel**: `trade_signals_high`\n- Importance: `IMPORTANCE_HIGH` (heads-up display)\n- Sound: enabled by default\n- Vibration: enabled\n\n### 4.2 Slack Webhook\n\n- Webhook URL stored in environment variable `SLACK_SIGNAL_WEBHOOK_URL`\n- POST to webhook URL when signal fires\n- Include paper trading disclaimer until live trading is approved\n- Failures are logged but do not block mobile delivery\n\n### 4.3 Delivery Priority\n\n1. Mobile push (immediate, highest priority)\n2. Slack webhook (fire-and-forget, async)\n\n---\n\n## 5. Frequency Limits (Anti-Spam)\n\nThese limits prevent alert fatigue:\n\n| Scope | Limit | Window |\n|-------|-------|--------|\n| Same market + same side | 1 notification | 15 minutes |\n| Global (all markets combined) | 5 notifications | 60 minutes |\n| Per-user quiet hours | 0 notifications | 22:00–07:00 local time (configurable) |\n| Burst guard | 3 notifications | 5 minutes |\n\n**Cooldown logic:**\n```\nnotificationKey = \"{marketId}:{side}:{signalType}\"\nif lastNotified[notificationKey] exists AND (now - lastNotified[notificationKey]) < 15min:\n    skip — cooldown active\nelse:\n    fire notification\n    lastNotified[notificationKey] = now\n```\n\n**Hourly cap:**\n```\nhourlyCount = count of notifications fired in last 60 minutes\nif hourlyCount >= 5:\n    queue notification for next available slot (do not drop)\n    log: \"Hourly cap reached — notification queued\"\n```\n\n**Minimum confidence floor:** 0.80 (team consensus, see `public/consensus.md` entry #4). Never lower without backtesting.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Signal Evaluation Flow\n\n```\n[Signal Generator - port 3200]\n        │\n        ▼\n[GET /api/signals every 30s]\n        │\n        ▼\n[Filter: confidence >= 0.80?] ──No──▶ Drop\n        │ Yes\n        ▼\n[Filter: signalType == \"entry\"?] ──No──▶ Drop\n        │ Yes\n        ▼\n[Check cooldown: same marketId+side notified < 15 min ago?] ──Yes──▶ Skip\n        │ No\n        ▼\n[Check hourly cap: >= 5 in last 60 min?] ──Yes──▶ Queue\n        │ No\n        ▼\n[Build notification payload (§3)]\n        │\n        ├──▶ [Send APNs / FCM]\n        │\n        └──▶ [POST Slack webhook] (async, non-blocking)\n        │\n        ▼\n[Update lastNotified[key] = now]\n[Increment hourly counter]\n[Log delivery result]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Implementation Notes\n\n### Notification Service (suggested module: `agents/bob/backend/notification_service.js`)\n\n```javascript\n// Key environment variables\nAPNS_KEY_ID=...          // Apple key ID\nAPNS_TEAM_ID=...         // Apple team ID\nAPNS_KEY_PATH=...        // Path to .p8 key file\nAPNS_BUNDLE_ID=...       // com.agentplanet.app\nFCM_SERVER_KEY=...       // Firebase server key\nSLACK_SIGNAL_WEBHOOK_URL=...\n\n// Polling interval\nconst SIGNAL_POLL_INTERVAL_MS = 30_000; // 30 seconds\n\n// Thresholds\nconst MIN_CONFIDENCE = 0.80;\nconst COOLDOWN_MS = 15 * 60 * 1000;     // 15 minutes\nconst HOURLY_CAP = 5;\nconst BURST_CAP = 3;\nconst BURST_WINDOW_MS = 5 * 60 * 1000;\n```\n\n### Deep Linking\n\nApp must handle `agentplanet://signals/{marketId}` to open the signal detail screen.\n\n### Offline Handling\n\nIf the app is offline when a push arrives:\n- iOS: APNs stores the most recent notification per `apns-collapse-id: \"signal-{marketId}\"` — stale signals are replaced, not stacked.\n- Android: FCM stores latest per `collapse_key: \"signal-{marketId}\"`.\n\nSet `apns-expiration: 300` (5 minutes) — signals older than 5 minutes are irrelevant by the time the user sees them.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Paper Trading Disclaimer\n\nPer team consensus (`public/consensus.md` entry #1): all trading is in paper mode until live credentials are obtained. Push notifications must include context:\n\n- Mobile: Add subtitle \"Paper Trade · Not a live order\" when `executed: false`\n- Slack: Append \"Paper trading mode\" in context block\n\n---\n\n## 9. Open Questions for Bob/Mia\n\n1. **Auth token for device registration**: How will mobile devices register their push tokens with the backend? Suggest `POST /api/notifications/register` with `{ deviceToken, platform, userId }`.\n2. **User preferences**: Should users be able to filter by strategy, market category, or minimum edge? If yes, Bob needs a preferences store.\n3. **Webhook URL management**: One global Slack webhook or per-user? Suggest starting with global.\n\n---\n\n## 10. Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Notifications fire only for signals with `confidence >= 0.80`\n- [ ] Same market+side is not notified more than once per 15 minutes\n- [ ] Global cap of 5 notifications/hour is enforced\n- [ ] APNs payload validates against Apple's notification spec\n- [ ] FCM payload uses `HIGH` priority with correct channel\n- [ ] Slack webhook payload renders correctly in Slack\n- [ ] Notifications include paper trading disclaimer while `executed: false`\n- [ ] Stale signals (>5 min) are collapsed, not stacked on device\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
