title\": \"Dismiss\",      \"destructive\": true }","+]","+```","+","+#### Android Notification Channel","+```","+channel_id:          trade_signals","+channel_name:        Trade Signals","+importance:          IMPORTANCE_HIGH","+sound:               signal_alert.wav","+vibration_pattern:   [0, 250, 250, 250]","+lights:              #00C853","+lock_screen:         VISIBILITY_PRIVATE","+```","+","+---","+"," ### 3.2 Slack Webhook Payload"," "," ```json"," {","-  \"text\": \"🟢 *Trade Signal Alert*\",","-  \"blocks\": [","+  \"text\": \":signal_strength: *Trade Signal: BTCW-26-JUN30-100K*\",","+  \"attachments\": [","     {","-      \"type\": \"header\",","-      \"text\": {","-        \"type\": \"plain_text\",","-        \"text\": \"📈 Trade Signal — BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\"","-      }","-    },","-    {","-      \"type\": \"section\",","+      \"color\": \"#00C853\",","       \"fields\": [","-        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Strategy:*\\nmean_reversion\" },","-        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Side:*\\nBUY YES\" },","-        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Confidence:*\\n95%\" },","-        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Expected Edge:*\\n+23¢ per contract\" },","-        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Recommended:*\\n29 contracts\" },","-        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Risk Amount:*\\n$18.56\" }","-      ]","-    },","-    {","-      \"type\": \"section\",","-      \"text\": {","-        \"type\": \"mrkdwn\",","-        \"text\": \"*Market:* Will Bitcoin exceed $100,000 by June 30, 2026?\\n*Reason:* Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890,000\\n*Current Price:* 64¢ YES\"","-      }","-    },","-    {","-      \"type\": \"context\",","-      \"elements\": [","-        {","-          \"type\": \"mrkdwn\",","-          \"text\": \"Generated at 2026-04-03T18:29:52Z · Paper trading mode\"","-        }","-      ]","+        { \"title\": \"Action\",      \"value\": \"BUY YES\",               \"short\": true },","+        { \"title\": \"Price\",       \"value\": \"64¢\",                   \"short\": true },","+        { \"title\": \"Confidence\",  \"value\": \"95%\",                   \"short\": true },","+        { \"title\": \"Edge\",        \"value\": \"+23%\",                  \"short\": true },","+        { \"title\": \"Contracts\",   \"value\": \"29 @ $1,856 risk\",      \"short\": true },","+        { \"title\": \"Strategy\",    \"value\": \"mean_reversion\",        \"short\": true },","+        { \"title\": \"Reason\",      \"value\": \"z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890k\", \"short\": false }","+      ],","+      \"footer\": \"Kalshi Alpha Dashboard\",","+      \"ts\": 1743705600","     }","   ]"," }"]},{"oldStart":155,"oldLines":166,"newStart":158,"newLines":167,"lines":[" "," ## 4. Delivery Channels"," ","-### 4.1 Mobile Push","+| Channel | When to Use | Config Key |","+|---------|-------------|------------|","+| Mobile Push (APNs) | User has iOS app + push permission granted | `channels.apns.enabled` |","+| Mobile Push (FCM) | User has Android app + push permission granted | `channels.fcm.enabled` |","+| Slack Webhook | Always enabled as fallback; useful for team monitoring | `channels.slack.enabled` |"," ","-| Platform | Service | Notes |","-|----------|---------|-------|","-| iOS | APNs (Apple Push Notification service) | `apns-priority: 10` for immediate delivery. TTL: 5 min (signals expire fast). Use `thread-id: \"trade_signals\"` to group notifications in Notification Center. |","-| Android | FCM (Firebase Cloud Messaging) | `priority: HIGH`, `channel_id: \"trade_signals_high\"` — users can mute per-channel without disabling all alerts. |","+**Fanout logic:** Send to ALL enabled channels concurrently. A failure on one channel does not block others. Log each delivery result independently."," ","-**iOS Notification Actions** (`category: \"TRADE_SIGNAL\"`):","-- **View Signal** — opens signal detail screen (deep link: `agentplanet://signals/{marketId}`)","-- **Dismiss** — no action","+```","+Signal generated","+      |","+      ├── confidence >= 0.80? → NO  → DROP (no notification)","+      |         YES ↓","+      ├── dedup check        → DUPLICATE → DROP","+      |         NEW ↓","+      ├── rate limit check   → SUPPRESSED → queue or DROP (see §5)","+      |         ALLOWED ↓","+      ├── [APNs push]        → log result","+      ├── [FCM push]         → log result","+      └── [Slack webhook]    → log result","+```"," ","-**Android Notification Channel**: `trade_signals_high`","-- Importance: `IMPORTANCE_HIGH` (heads-up display)","-- Sound: enabled by default","-- Vibration: enabled","+---"," ","-### 4.2 Slack Webhook","+## 5. Frequency Limits (Anti-Spam)"," ","-- Webhook URL stored in environment variable `SLACK_SIGNAL_WEBHOOK_URL`","-- POST to webhook URL when signal fires","-- Include paper trading disclaimer until live trading is approved","-- Failures are logged but do not block mobile delivery","+Mobile notifications must never feel like spam. The following limits apply **per user**:"," ","-### 4.3 Delivery Priority","+| Rule | Limit | Behavior when exceeded |","+|------|-------|------------------------|","+| Per-market cooldown | 1 notification per `(marketId, side)` per **15 minutes** | Drop duplicate signal |","+| Global burst limit | Max **5 notifications** per **1 hour** | Queue; deliver after cooldown clears |","+| Daily cap | Max **20 notifications** per **24 hours** | Drop excess; log as suppressed |","+| Quiet hours | No push between **22:00–07:00** user local time | Slack only; push deferred to 07:00 |"," ","-1. Mobile push (immediate, highest priority)","-2. Slack webhook (fire-and-forget, async)","+**Dedup key:** `SHA256( marketId + signalType + side + floor(generatedAt / 900s) )`","+— Same signal within the same 15-min window is a duplicate regardless of minor confidence drift."," ","+**Queue behavior:** Suppressed notifications are held in a delivery queue (max 10 items). When the rate window clears, only the **highest-confidence** queued signal per market is delivered; signals older than 30 minutes are discarded undelivered.","+"," ---"," ","-## 5. Frequency Limits (Anti-Spam)","+## 6. Signal Polling / Delivery Architecture"," ","-These limits prevent alert fatigue:","+The signal engine (`GET /api/signals` on port 3200) is polled rather than streaming. Recommended architecture:"," ","-| Scope | Limit | Window |","-|-------|-------|--------|","-| Same market + same side | 1 notification | 15 minutes |","-| Global (all markets combined) | 5 notifications | 60 minutes |","-| Per-user quiet hours | 0 notifications | 22:00–07:00 local time (configurable) |","-| Burst guard | 3 notifications | 5 minutes |","-","-**Cooldown logic:**"," ```","-notificationKey = \"{marketId}:{side}:{signalType}\"","-if lastNotified[notificationKey] exists AND (now - lastNotified[notificationKey]) < 15min:","-    skip — cooldown active","-else:","-    fire notification","-    lastNotified[notificationKey] = now","+┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐","+│  Signal Poller (server-side, runs in        │","+│  monitor.js or a dedicated notifier.js)     │","+│                                             │","+│  Every 60s:                                 │","+│    1. GET localhost:3200/api/signals        │","+│    2. For each signal with conf >= 0.80:    │","+│       a. Check dedup store (SQLite)         │","+│       b. Check rate limits per user         │","+│       c. Fan out to APNs + FCM + Slack      │","+│    3. Log all results                       │","+└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘","+         │              │              │","+         ▼              ▼              ▼","+    APNs Gateway   FCM Gateway   Slack Webhook","+         │              │","+         ▼              ▼","+     iOS Device   Android Device"," ```"," ","-**Hourly cap:**","-```","-hourlyCount = count of notifications fired in last 60 minutes","-if hourlyCount >= 5:","-    queue notification for next available slot (do not drop)","-    log: \"Hourly cap reached — notification queued\"","-```","+**Poll interval:** 60 seconds (signals update on this cadence per live_runner.js)."," ","-**Minimum confidence floor:** 0.80 (team consensus, see `public/consensus.md` entry #4). Never lower without backtesting.","+**Dedup store schema (SQLite):**","+```sql","+CREATE TABLE notified_signals (","+  dedup_key     TEXT PRIMARY KEY,","+  market_id     TEXT NOT NULL,","+  signal_type   TEXT NOT NULL,","+  side          TEXT NOT NULL,","+  confidence    REAL NOT NULL,","+  notified_at   INTEGER NOT NULL,   -- unix timestamp","+  channels      TEXT NOT NULL        -- JSON array: [\"apns\",\"fcm\",\"slack\"]","+);"," ","+CREATE TABLE notification_rate (","+  user_id       TEXT NOT NULL,","+  window_start  INTEGER NOT NULL,   -- unix timestamp, floor to hour","+  count         INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,","+  PRIMARY KEY (user_id, window_start)","+);","+```","+"," ---"," ","-## 6. Signal Evaluation Flow","+## 7. Device Registration & Token Management"," "," ```","-[Signal Generator - port 3200]","-        │","-        ▼","-[GET /api/signals every 30s]","-        │","-        ▼","-[Filter: confidence >= 0.80?] ──No──▶ Drop","-        │ Yes","-        ▼","-[Filter: signalType == \"entry\"?] ──No──▶ Drop","-        │ Yes","-        ▼","-[Check cooldown: same marketId+side notified < 15 min ago?] ──Yes──▶ Skip","-        │ No","-        ▼","-[Check hourly cap: >= 5 in last 60 min?] ──Yes──▶ Queue","-        │ No","-        ▼","-[Build notification payload (§3)]","-        │","-        ├──▶ [Send APNs / FCM]","-        │","-        └──▶ [POST Slack webhook] (async, non-blocking)","-        │","-        ▼","-[Update lastNotified[key] = now]","-[Increment hourly counter]","-[Log delivery result]","+POST /api/notifications/register","+Authorization: Bearer <token>","+{","+  \"userId\": \"string\",","+  \"platform\": \"ios\" | \"android\",","+  \"pushToken\": \"string\",    // APNs device token or FCM registration token","+  \"appVersion\": \"string\",","+  \"osVersion\": \"string\"","+}","+→ 200 { \"ok\": true, \"registeredAt\": \"...\" }"," ```"," ","+**Token lifecycle:**","+- Store in `notification_devices` table","+- On APNs `BadDeviceToken` or FCM `UNREGISTERED` error → delete token immediately","+- Refresh token on each app launch (tokens rotate on OS reinstall)","+- Tokens inactive for **90 days** → mark inactive, skip delivery","+"," ---"," ","-## 7. Implementation Notes","+## 8. Notification Tap Deep Link"," ","-### Notification Service (suggested module: `agents/bob/backend/notification_service.js`)","+When user taps a notification, the app opens to the signal detail view:"," ","-```javascript","-// Key environment variables","-APNS_KEY_ID=...          // Apple key ID","-APNS_TEAM_ID=...         // Apple team ID","-APNS_KEY_PATH=...        // Path to .p8 key file","-APNS_BUNDLE_ID=...       // com.agentplanet.app","-FCM_SERVER_KEY=...       // Firebase server key","-SLACK_SIGNAL_WEBHOOK_URL=...","-","-// Polling interval","-const SIGNAL_POLL_INTERVAL_MS = 30_000; // 30 seconds","-","-// Thresholds","-const MIN_CONFIDENCE = 0.80;","-const COOLDOWN_MS = 15 * 60 * 1000;     // 15 minutes","-const HOURLY_CAP = 5;","-const BURST_CAP = 3;","-const BURST_WINDOW_MS = 5 * 60 * 1000;"," ```","+kalshidash://signal/{marketId}/{signalType}","+```"," ","-### Deep Linking","+Example: `kalshidash://signal/m4/entry`"," ","-App must handle `agentplanet://signals/{marketId}` to open the signal detail screen.","+The detail view shows:","+- Market title + ticker","+- Signal side, price, edge, confidence","+- Recommended contracts + risk amount","+- Strategy reasoning (`reason` field)","+- CTA: \"Open Kalshi\" → deep link into Kalshi app/web"," ","-### Offline Handling","-","-If the app is offline when a push arrives:","-- iOS: APNs stores the most recent notification per `apns-collapse-id: \"signal-{marketId}\"` — stale signals are replaced, not stacked.","-- Android: FCM stores latest per `collapse_key: \"signal-{marketId}\"`.","-","-Set `apns-expiration: 300` (5 minutes) — signals older than 5 minutes are irrelevant by the time the user sees them.","-"," ---"," ","-## 8. Paper Trading Disclaimer","+## 9. Notification Permission Strategy (iOS)"," ","-Per team consensus (`public/consensus.md` entry #1): all trading is in paper mode until live credentials are obtained. Push notifications must include context:","+**Do NOT request permission on first launch.** Earn it first."," ","-- Mobile: Add subtitle \"Paper Trade · Not a live order\" when `executed: false`","-- Slack: Append \"Paper trading mode\" in context block","+1. Show value: display 2–3 signal alerts as in-app banners (no system prompt yet)","+2. At third in-app signal, show a custom pre-permission screen: \"Get alerts when high-confidence signals appear — even when the app is closed\"","+3. Only then call `requestAuthorization(options: [.alert, .sound, .badge])`","+4. If denied: fall back to in-app banners + Slack only; re-ask after 30 days if user views signals 3+ times"," ","+**Android:** Request `POST_NOTIFICATIONS` permission (Android 13+) using the same two-step pattern.","+"," ---"," ","-## 9. Open Questions for Bob/Mia","+## 10. Notes for API Owners (Bob / Mia)"," ","-1. **Auth token for device registration**: How will mobile devices register their push tokens with the backend? Suggest `POST /api/notifications/register` with `{ deviceToken, platform, userId }`.","-2. **User preferences**: Should users be able to filter by strategy, market category, or minimum edge? If yes, Bob needs a preferences store.","-3. **Webhook URL management**: One global Slack webhook or per-user? Suggest starting with global.","+- The existing `GET /api/signals` payload contains everything needed (ticker, confidence, edge, reason, contracts, risk). No new endpoint required for v1.","+- Future: consider `GET /api/signals/stream` (SSE) to eliminate the 60s polling lag.","+- Auth: the notification registration endpoint must require `Authorization: Bearer` header (per consensus.md rule #3)."," "," ---"," ","-## 10. Acceptance Criteria","+## 11. Open Questions / Future Work"," ","-- [ ] Notifications fire only for signals with `confidence >= 0.80`","-- [ ] Same market+side is not notified more than once per 15 minutes","-- [ ] Global cap of 5 notifications/hour is enforced","-- [ ] APNs payload validates against Apple's notification spec","-- [ ] FCM payload uses `HIGH` priority with correct channel","-- [ ] Slack webhook payload renders correctly in Slack","-- [ ] Notifications include paper trading disclaimer while `executed: false`","-- [ ] Stale signals (>5 min) are collapsed, not stacked on device","+| Item | Owner | Priority |","+|------|-------|----------|","+| APNs certificate provisioning | Judy + Eve | High |","+| FCM project credentials | Judy + Eve | High |","+| Slack webhook URL for prod | Alice/CEO | High |","+| Push permission opt-in analytics | Judy + Grace | Medium |","+| Exit signal notifications (`signalType=\"exit\"`) | Judy | Low |","+| SSE streaming endpoint | Bob/Mia | Low |"]}],"originalFile":"# Push Notification Spec — Trade Signal Alerts\n\n**Author:** Judy (Mobile Engineer)\n**Date:** 2026-04-03\n**Task:** T268\n**Status:** Final\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overview\n\nThis spec defines the push notification system for Kalshi trade signal alerts. Notifications fire when the trading pipeline generates high-confidence signals (≥80% confidence, per team consensus). Users are alerted on mobile (iOS/Android) and optionally via Slack webhook.\n\nSignal source: `GET http://localhost:3200/api/signals`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Trigger Conditions\n\nA notification is triggered when **all** of the following are true:\n\n| Condition | Rule |\n|-----------|------|\n| Signal confidence | `confidence >= 0.80` (team consensus minimum) |\n| Signal type | `signalType == \"entry\"` (not exit or hold) |\n| Market not already notified | No notification sent for same `marketId` + `side` in the last **15 minutes** |\n| Frequency limit not exceeded | Global cap: max **5 notifications per hour** across all markets |\n| Trading not in cooldown | Respect per-market cooldown window (see §5) |\n\n**Example triggering signal** (from live API):\n```json\n{\n  \"strategy\": \"mean_reversion\",\n  \"marketId\": \"m4\",\n  \"ticker\": \"BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\",\n  \"side\": \"yes\",\n  \"signalType\": \"entry\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"expectedEdge\": 23,\n  \"recommendedContracts\": 29,\n  \"riskAmount\": 1856,\n  \"reason\": \"Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890000\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Notification Payload Schema\n\n### 3.1 Mobile Push (APNs / FCM)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"notification\": {\n    \"title\": \"Trade Signal — BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\",\n    \"body\": \"BUY YES · 95% confidence · Edge: +23¢ · 29 contracts recommended\"\n  },\n  \"data\": {\n    \"type\": \"trade_signal\",\n    \"version\": \"1\",\n    \"marketId\": \"m4\",\n    \"ticker\": \"BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\",\n    \"marketTitle\": \"Will Bitcoin exceed $100,000 by June 30, 2026?\",\n    \"strategy\": \"mean_reversion\",\n    \"side\": \"yes\",\n    \"signalType\": \"entry\",\n    \"confidence\": 0.95,\n    \"expectedEdge\": 23,\n    \"currentPrice\": 64,\n    \"targetPrice\": 64,\n    \"recommendedContracts\": 29,\n    \"riskAmount\": 1856,\n    \"reason\": \"Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890000\",\n    \"generatedAt\": \"2026-04-03T18:29:52.840Z\",\n    \"deepLink\": \"agentplanet://signals/m4\"\n  },\n  \"apns\": {\n    \"headers\": {\n      \"apns-priority\": \"10\",\n      \"apns-push-type\": \"alert\",\n      \"apns-expiration\": \"300\"\n    },\n    \"payload\": {\n      \"aps\": {\n        \"alert\": {\n          \"title\": \"Trade Signal — BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\",\n          \"body\": \"BUY YES · 95% confidence · Edge: +23¢ · 29 contracts recommended\"\n        },\n        \"sound\": \"default\",\n        \"badge\": 1,\n        \"thread-id\": \"trade_signals\",\n        \"category\": \"TRADE_SIGNAL\",\n        \"mutable-content\": 1\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"android\": {\n    \"priority\": \"HIGH\",\n    \"ttl\": \"300s\",\n    \"notification\": {\n      \"channel_id\": \"trade_signals_high\",\n      \"icon\": \"ic_signal_alert\",\n      \"color\": \"#00C853\",\n      \"click_action\": \"OPEN_SIGNAL_DETAIL\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 3.2 Slack Webhook Payload\n\n```json\n{\n  \"text\": \"🟢 *Trade Signal Alert*\",\n  \"blocks\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"header\",\n      \"text\": {\n        \"type\": \"plain_text\",\n        \"text\": \"📈 Trade Signal — BTCW-26-JUN30-100K\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"section\",\n      \"fields\": [\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Strategy:*\\nmean_reversion\" },\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Side:*\\nBUY YES\" },\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Confidence:*\\n95%\" },\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Expected Edge:*\\n+23¢ per contract\" },\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Recommended:*\\n29 contracts\" },\n        { \"type\": \"mrkdwn\", \"text\": \"*Risk Amount:*\\n$18.56\" }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"section\",\n      \"text\": {\n        \"type\": \"mrkdwn\",\n        \"text\": \"*Market:* Will Bitcoin exceed $100,000 by June 30, 2026?\\n*Reason:* Mean reversion: z-score=-10.72, mean=86.7, vol=890,000\\n*Current Price:* 64¢ YES\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"context\",\n      \"elements\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"mrkdwn\",\n          \"text\": \"Generated at 2026-04-03T18:29:52Z · Paper trading mode\"\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Delivery Channels\n\n### 4.1 Mobile Push\n\n| Platform | Service | Notes |\n|----------|---------|-------|\n| iOS | APNs (Apple Push Notification service) | `apns-priority: 10` for immediate delivery. TTL: 5 min (signals expire fast). Use `thread-id: \"trade_signals\"` to group notifications in Notification Center. |\n| Android | FCM (Firebase Cloud Messaging) | `priority: HIGH`, `channel_id: \"trade_signals_high\"` — users can mute per-channel without disabling all alerts. |\n\n**iOS Notification Actions** (`category: \"TRADE_SIGNAL\"`):\n- **View Signal** — opens signal detail screen (deep link: `agentplanet://signals/{marketId}`)\n- **Dismiss** — no action\n\n**Android Notification Channel**: `trade_signals_high`\n- Importance: `IMPORTANCE_HIGH` (heads-up display)\n- Sound: enabled by default\n- Vibration: enabled\n\n### 4.2 Slack Webhook\n\n- Webhook URL stored in environment variable `SLACK_SIGNAL_WEBHOOK_URL`\n- POST to webhook URL when signal fires\n- Include paper trading disclaimer until live trading is approved\n- Failures are logged but do not block mobile delivery\n\n### 4.3 Delivery Priority\n\n1. Mobile push (immediate, highest priority)\n2. Slack webhook (fire-and-forget, async)\n\n---\n\n## 5. Frequency Limits (Anti-Spam)\n\nThese limits prevent alert fatigue:\n\n| Scope | Limit | Window |\n|-------|-------|--------|\n| Same market + same side | 1 notification | 15 minutes |\n| Global (all markets combined) | 5 notifications | 60 minutes |\n| Per-user quiet hours | 0 notifications | 22:00–07:00 local time (configurable) |\n| Burst guard | 3 notifications | 5 minutes |\n\n**Cooldown logic:**\n```\nnotificationKey = \"{marketId}:{side}:{signalType}\"\nif lastNotified[notificationKey] exists AND (now - lastNotified[notificationKey]) < 15min:\n    skip — cooldown active\nelse:\n    fire notification\n    lastNotified[notificationKey] = now\n```\n\n**Hourly cap:**\n```\nhourlyCount = count of notifications fired in last 60 minutes\nif hourlyCount >= 5:\n    queue notification for next available slot (do not drop)\n    log: \"Hourly cap reached — notification queued\"\n```\n\n**Minimum confidence floor:** 0.80 (team consensus, see `public/consensus.md` entry #4). Never lower without backtesting.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Signal Evaluation Flow\n\n```\n[Signal Generator - port 3200]\n        │\n        ▼\n[GET /api/signals every 30s]\n        │\n        ▼\n[Filter: confidence >= 0.80?] ──No──▶ Drop\n        │ Yes\n        ▼\n[Filter: signalType == \"entry\"?] ──No──▶ Drop\n        │ Yes\n        ▼\n[Check cooldown: same marketId+side notified < 15 min ago?] ──Yes──▶ Skip\n        │ No\n        ▼\n[Check hourly cap: >= 5 in last 60 min?] ──Yes──▶ Queue\n        │ No\n        ▼\n[Build notification payload (§3)]\n        │\n        ├──▶ [Send APNs / FCM]\n        │\n        └──▶ [POST Slack webhook] (async, non-blocking)\n        │\n        ▼\n[Update lastNotified[key] = now]\n[Increment hourly counter]\n[Log delivery result]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Implementation Notes\n\n### Notification Service (suggested module: `agents/bob/backend/notification_service.js`)\n\n```javascript\n// Key environment variables\nAPNS_KEY_ID=...          // Apple key ID\nAPNS_TEAM_ID=...         // Apple team ID\nAPNS_KEY_PATH=...        // Path to .p8 key file\nAPNS_BUNDLE_ID=...       // com.agentplanet.app\nFCM_SERVER_KEY=...       // Firebase server key\nSLACK_SIGNAL_WEBHOOK_URL=...\n\n// Polling interval\nconst SIGNAL_POLL_INTERVAL_MS = 30_000; // 30 seconds\n\n// Thresholds\nconst MIN_CONFIDENCE = 0.80;\nconst COOLDOWN_MS = 15 * 60 * 1000;     // 15 minutes\nconst HOURLY_CAP = 5;\nconst BURST_CAP = 3;\nconst BURST_WINDOW_MS = 5 * 60 * 1000;\n```\n\n### Deep Linking\n\nApp must handle `agentplanet://signals/{marketId}` to open the signal detail screen.\n\n### Offline Handling\n\nIf the app is offline when a push arrives:\n- iOS: APNs stores the most recent notification per `apns-collapse-id: \"signal-{marketId}\"` — stale signals are replaced, not stacked.\n- Android: FCM stores latest per `collapse_key: \"signal-{marketId}\"`.\n\nSet `apns-expiration: 300` (5 minutes) — signals older than 5 minutes are irrelevant by the time the user sees them.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Paper Trading Disclaimer\n\nPer team consensus (`public/consensus.md` entry #1): all trading is in paper mode until live credentials are obtained. Push notifications must include context:\n\n- Mobile: Add subtitle \"Paper Trade · Not a live order\" when `executed: false`\n- Slack: Append \"Paper trading mode\" in context block\n\n---\n\n## 9. Open Questions for Bob/Mia\n\n1. **Auth token for device registration**: How will mobile devices register their push tokens with the backend? Suggest `POST /api/notifications/register` with `{ deviceToken, platform, userId }`.\n2. **User preferences**: Should users be able to filter by strategy, market category, or minimum edge? If yes, Bob needs a preferences store.\n3. **Webhook URL management**: One global Slack webhook or per-user? Suggest starting with global.\n\n---\n\n## 10. Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Notifications fire only for signals with `confidence >= 0.80`\n- [ ] Same market+side is not notified more than once per 15 minutes\n- [ ] Global cap of 5 notifications/hour is enforced\n- [ ] APNs payload validates against Apple's notification spec\n- [ ] FCM payload uses `HIGH` priority with correct channel\n- [ ] Slack webhook payload renders correctly in Slack\n- [ ] Notifications include paper trading disclaimer while `executed: false`\n- [ ] Stale signals (>5 min) are collapsed, not stacked on device\n"}}
